    <p>{`If you're running a distributed GraphQL infrastructure, where federated services `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://www.warthog.dev/docs/warthog-server/federation/federation-spec/#fetch-service-capabilities"
      }}>{`compose`}</a>{` to form a complete schema, tracking the history of the graph and its underlying services is essential. Running `}<code parentName="p" {...{
        "className": "language-text"
      }}>{`warthog service:push`}</code>{` from within CI/CD on any federated service registers the overall schema of the graph and updates the graph's `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "#managed-configuration"
